article.headline: Miami (Ohio) 53, Toledo 40
article.story: OXFORD, Ohio -- Michael Bramos paced Miami of Ohio with 15 points as the RedHawks scored first and never trailed Saturday, beating Toledo 53-40. Tyler Dierkers had 10 points and 15 rebounds, and Nick Winbush added 10 points for Miami (14-7, 7-2 Mid-American Conference). Mohamed Lo scored 13 points for Toledo (4-19, 2-7), and Justin Anyijong had 10. Eric Pollitz broke the ice for Miami with a jumper at the 16:28 mark, and the only other time the Rockets got within 2 points was when Lo converted a pair of free throws two minutes later. After that, Miami widened its lead to 30-15 at halftime and never let Toledo get closer than 12 after that. Cold shooting hurt Toledo early as the Rockets hit just 22 percent from the field in the first half.
